        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 6:31AM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 630 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Spearville to near Ford. Movement was east
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Spearville and Ford around 635 AM CDT.
Bellefont around 645 AM CDT.
Windhorst around 650 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
